window.docContents[120].resolve({"/Basic-Types/Booleans/#zh-basictypes-h006":{"contents":"Boolean Infix Operators中缀运算符 &&、|| 和 ^^ 分别是 Bool.and、Bool.or 和 Bool.xor 的表示法。\n\nBoolean Negation前缀运算符 ! 是 Bool.not 的表示法。\n\n","context":"Lean 参考\u0009基本类型\u0009布尔值","header":"20.11.3. 句法","id":"/Basic-Types/Booleans/#zh-basictypes-h006"},"/Basic-Types/Byte-Arrays/#zh-basictypes-bytearray-h006":{"contents":"Decodes a sequence of characters from their UTF-8 representation. Returns none if the bytes are\nnot a sequence of Unicode scalar values.\n\nDecodes and returns the Char whose UTF-8 encoding begins at i in bytes.Returns none if i is not the start of a valid UTF-8 encoding of a character.\n\nDecodes and returns the Char whose UTF-8 encoding begins at i in bytes.This function requires a proof that there is, in fact, a valid Char at i. utf8DecodeChar? is\nan alternative function that returns Option Char instead of requiring a proof ahead of time.\n\n","context":"Lean 参考\u0009基本类型\u0009字节吞吐量\u0009API 参考\u0009转换","header":"20.17.1.4.1. UTF-8","id":"/Basic-Types/Byte-Arrays/#zh-basictypes-bytearray-h006"},"/Basic-Types/Strings/#string-api-valid-pos":{"contents":"A Pos s is a byte offset in s together with a proof that this position is at a UTF-8\ncharacter boundary.The underlying byte offset of the Pos.The proof that offset is valid for the string s.\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n","context":"Lean 参考\u0009基本类型\u0009弦乐\u0009API 参考","header":"20.8.4.4. 职位","id":"/Basic-Types/Strings/#string-api-valid-pos"},"/Functors___-Monads-and-___do___-Notation/API-Reference/#zh-monads-api-h002":{"contents":"If the proposition p is true, does nothing, else fails (using failure).\n\nReturns some x if f succeeds with value x, else returns none.\n\n","context":"Lean 参考\u0009函子、Monad 和  do  表示法\u0009API 参考","header":"18.4.2. 控制流程","id":"/Functors___-Monads-and-___do___-Notation/API-Reference/#zh-monads-api-h002"},"/Iterators/Iterator-Definitions/#zh-iterators-h007":{"contents":"为了使迭代器的 宇宙层级 更加灵活，在 Iterator.step 的结果周围应用了包装类型 Shrink。\n该类型目前是占位符。\n当完整实施可用时，它的存在是为了减少重大变更的范围。\n\nCurrently, Shrink α is just a wrapper around α.In the future, Shrink should allow shrinking α into a potentially smaller universe,\ngiven a proof that α is actually small, just like Mathlib's Shrink, except that\nthe latter's conversion functions are noncomputable. Until then, Shrink α is always in the\nsame universe as α.This no-op type exists so that fewer breaking changes will be needed when the\nreal Shrink type is available and the iterators will be made more flexible with regard to\nuniverses.The conversion functions Shrink.deflate and\nShrink.inflate form an equivalence between\nα and Shrink α, but this equivalence is intentionally not definitional.\n\nConverts elements of Shrink α into elements of α.\n\nConverts elements of α into elements of Shrink α.\n\n","context":"Lean 参考\u0009迭代器\u0009迭代器定义","header":"22.2.5. 宇宙层级","id":"/Iterators/Iterator-Definitions/#zh-iterators-h007"}});